Asymptote 是一种描述性[[矢量图形|矢量图形]]语言，由 Andy Hammerlindl, John C. Bowman (University of Alberta)，与 Tom Prince 开发。它提供了一种自然的基于坐标的工程绘图。Asymptot 适用于所有主流平台（[[UNIX|UNIX]]、[[Mac_OS|Mac OS]]，[[Microsoft_Windows|Microsoft Windows]]）。它是一款[[免费软件|免费软件]]，以 [[GNU宽通用公共许可证|GNU宽通用公共许可证]]发布。

==语法和特点==
Asymptote 用 LaTeX 输入标签和公式，输出高质量 [[PostScript|PostScript]]、[[PDF|PDF]]、[[SVG|SVG]]或 [[3D_PRC|3D PRC]] 文件<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asyTUG.pdf |title=Asymptote: A vector graphics language, J. C. Bowman and A. Hammerlindl, TUGBOAT: The Communications of the TeX Users Group, 29:2, 288-294 (2008). |accessdate=2010-12-12 |archive-date=2011-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717114952/http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asyTUG.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。它受 [[Metapost|Metapost]] 启发，但语法类似于 [[C++|C++]]。它给出了一种输入数学图形的标准，就像 TeX/LaTeX 成为了输入公式的标准。它是数学导向的（例如向量的旋转是[[复数_(数学)|复数乘法]]），并利用[[单纯形方法|单纯形方法]]和 deferred drawing 来解决固定大小对象（标签和箭头）和需随图形大小缩放对象的总体大小约束问题。Asymptote 将 Metapost 的路径构造算法完全扩展到三维<ref>[http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asy3d.pdf The 3D Asymptote Generalization of MetaPost Bézier Interpolation, J. C. Bowman, Proceedings in Applied Mathematics and Mechanics, 7:1, 2010021-2010022 (2007)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asy3d.pdf |date=20110717115026 }}.</ref>，并把命令编译为真正的机器编码且不牺牲可移植性。Asymptote 本身实现了高级图形命令，允许它们为特定的用途定制。它还是第一个将 TeX 提升为三维的软件<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asyTUG3.pdf |title=Asymptote: Lifting TeX to three dimensions, J. C. Bowman and Orest Shardt, TUGBOAT: The Communications of the TeX Users Group, 30:1, 58-63 (2009). |accessdate=2010-12-12 |archive-date=2011-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110401112438/http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/asyTUG3.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/cad10.pdf |title=Surface Parametrization of Nonsimply Connected Planar Bézier Regions, O. Shardt and J. C. Bowman, submitted to Computer Aided Design (2010). |accessdate=2010-12-12 |archive-date=2011-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110401112540/http://www.math.ualberta.ca/~bowman/publications/cad10.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
